com.zhukovsd.graphs

Class Graph<E extends Vertex<E>>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.zhukovsd.graphs.Graph<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - type of vertex in graph
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DualGraph, EmbeddedGraph, SubGraph

    public class Graph<E extends Vertex<E>>
extends java.lang.Object
    Basic graph implementation. Graph consists of vertexes and pairs of opposite-directional edges between them. If vertex A connected to vertex B, then vertex A holds edge AB, and vertex B holds edge BA. Situations, when A connected to B, but B not connected to A, are not allowed.
